  "doc_id": "11628",
  "text": "Haemophilus phage HP1 correlated with caries and health, respectively, another novel finding. Interestingly, Streptococcus phage M102 is specific for S. mutans serotype C [CITATION_1] , the most common serotype of S. mutans. Given that the phage and its host were co-detected, the former may have occurred as prophage. Thus, Streptococcus phage M102 may act as a marker for S. mutans serotype C and could then be targeted to induce lysis of S. mutans, a potential prevention strategy of dental caries that is worth exploring.",
